  PxDMX and PxGIZMA (c) 1994  Randolph Beck
  =================


  PxDMX  --Paradox Data Editing Unit for tvDMX
  =====

    Borland's Paradox Engine is required to use this unit.
    See program PXSHOP.PAS for sample code.


  Network Available Constant
  --------------------------

    NetInit       :  boolean  =  FALSE;

	Set by TDmxPxEditor and TDmxParadox objects during object
	construction if network-related procedures should be used.


  Memo Editing Constants
  ----------------------

    cmDMX_EditMemo		=  cmDMX + 35;
    hcPxMemo	  : word	=  hcNoContext;


    StdMemoSize	  : word	=  4094;
    StdMemoRect	  : TRect	=  (A:(X:10;Y:3);B:(X:70;Y:17));
    MemoZoomRect  : TRect	=  (A:(X:10;Y:3);B:(X:70;Y:17));

    BlankFields	  : boolean	=  TRUE;
    Auto1900	  : boolean	=  TRUE;

    PxDelimiter	  : char	=  '|';
    PxCommands	  : TCommandSet	=  [];



  Template Design Constants
  -------------------------

    fldPxSTRING   : char        =  's';
    fldPxNUMBER   : string[31]	=  'r,rrr,rrr.rrrrr';
    fldPxCURRENCY : string[31]	=  '($rrr,rrr.zz)';
    fldPxSHORTNUM : string[31]	=  'iii,iii ';

    fldPxDATE     : string[63]	=  ' WW-'^F + ^U+char(12) +
				  #0'ZW-'   + ^U+char(31) +
				  #0'ZZZW '^F;

	These typed-constants are used by the TDmxParadox constructor
	to build a template string.  Note how program PXSHOP.PAS changes
	these during initialization.  See the TDmxParadox.FieldTemplate
        method to customize templates for individual fields.


  PxDMX Global Functions
  ----------------------

  function  PxDmxFieldTemplate(FName,FType: NameString) : string;

	Returns a template string for the given field name and type.
	procedure is called by TDmxParadox.FieldTemplate().


  function  PxEntryFields(Px: TableHandle; DMX: PDmxParadox) : PSItem;

	Returns a pointer to a TSItem string-item chain of template codes
	which can be used by the EntryBox() function.

        The DMX parameter can be a NIL to use the unit's default tvDMX
        template design constants (see fldXXXX above).

	If DMX is not NIL, the DMX^.FieldTemplate() method will be called
        to create specialized templates.



  Object Types
  ------------

    TDmxPxEditor        =  OBJECT(TDmxEditBuf)

	This is a simple object that displays data from a Paradox table.
	The table must already be open, and a pointer to the table-handle
	is passed in the AData pointer.  Your program must provide a valid
	template-string to match the assigned table.  Its constructor uses
	the same syntax as TDmxEditBuf.Init().
	The constructor's BSize parameter can be set to the maximum number
	of records you want to permit entered, or to zero if you want no
	set limit.  (Note that this version is still limited to editing
	32765 records.)
    
    
    TDmxPxWindow  =  OBJECT(TDmxExpBufWin)

	This is a TDmxWindow derivative that initializes a TDmxPxEditor
	view.  Its constructor uses the same syntax as TDmxWindow.Init().


    TDmxParadox   =  OBJECT (TDmxPxEditor)

	This is a descendant of TDmxPxEditor that creates a template-
	string, using the fldPxXXXX template design constants (see above).
	It has this constructor:

	  constructor Init (var AData : TableHandle;  BSize : longint;
			    var Bounds : TRect;  ALabels,ARecInd : PDmxLink;
				AHScrollBar,AVScrollBar : PScrollBar);

	(See the TDmxPxLabels object below.)

	Template strings are assigned using this VIRTUAL method:

	  function  FieldTemplate (FName,FType : NameString) : string;

	This FieldTemplate() function is called internally for each field
	in the table, with FName and FType set to the field name and type
	(eg: "Customer" and "A32").  It returns a template-string for
	that field --using one of the fldPxXXXX design constants-- but
	your program can override this method to return a customized
	field template-string.


    TDmxPxLabels        =  OBJECT (TDmxExtLabels)

	This object is used instead of TDmxLabels objects to create a
	field-label string while TDmxParadox objects are constructed.
	This view must be initialized and inserted into the window
	before the TDmxParadox view is initialized.


    TDmxParadoxWin      =  OBJECT (TDmxExpBufWin)

	A TDmxWindow derivative that initializes a TDmxParadox view.


  PxGIZMA
  =======

  Px Sort-Order Constants
  -----------------------

    These values are returned by the PxTblInfo() and PxTblInfoBox()
    functions:

      PxAsciiSort	=  0;
      PxIntlSort	=  1;
      PxNorDanSort	=  2;
      PxNorDan4Sort	=  3;
      PxSwedFinSort	=  4;


  Global Functions
  ----------------

    function  DosErrToPxErr(Err: integer) : integer;

	Converts a DOS error code into an approximate PxERR_XXXX equivalent.

	Example:
	    If (PxErrorBox(DosErrToPxErr(IOResult)) = PxSuccess) then
	      begin
	      ...


    function  PxBuild(TblName: FNameStr; AFields: PSItem) : integer;

	Creates a Paradox table using field information in AFields.
	Each row contains a field name and field type.  A comma must
	be used to separate the field name from its type.  Fields in
	the primary key should be followed by an asterisk.  Secondary
	key fields (incremental only) should be followed by a plus.

	Example:
	  ErrCode := PxBuild('ACCOUNTS',
			NewSItem('Name, A25*',
			NewSItem('ID, N*+',
			NewSItem('Balance, $',
			NewSItem('Checked, S',
			NewSItem('Date, D+',
				nil)))))
			);


    function  PxErrorBox(Status: integer) : integer;

	Displays a Paradox error message in a message-box
	(does nothing if Status=Zero).

	Example:
	    If (PxErrorBox(PxRecBufOpen(TblH,Rec)) = PxSuccess) then
	      begin
	      ...


    function  PxPswAddBox : boolean;
    function  PxPswDelBox : boolean;

        Dialog box takes user input to add or remove a password.
        Returns TRUE if okay.


    function  PxTblInfo(TableName: FNameStr;  var Recs: longint;
			var Fields,KeyFields,SortOrder,VerID: integer;
			var Encrypted: boolean) : integer;

        Gets information about TableName.  Function returns an error code.


    function  PxTblInfoBox(TableName: FNameStr) : boolean;

	Dialog box displays information about TableName.  It returns FALSE
	if the table does not exist.


    function  PxSetDefaultsBox(HC,hOK,hCanx: word) : boolean;

	Dialog box to set Paradox defaults.  The parameters given may be
	used for help contexts:

	 HC:	Hint := 'Swap buffer size';
	 HC+1:	Hint := 'Maximum number of tables that can be open at once';
	 HC+2:	Hint := 'Maximum number of record buffers';
	 HC+3:	Hint := 'Maximum number of locks per table';
	 HC+4:	Hint := 'Maximum number of file handles available';
	 HC+5:	Hint := 'Case sensitive sorting; accented characters at end';
	 HC+6:	Hint := 'Sorted irrespective of case or special accents';
	 HC+7:	Hint := 'Special ligatures sorted after int''l sequence';
	 HC+8:	Hint := 'Norwegian/Danish sort sequence for Paradox 4.0';
	 HC+9:	Hint := 'Swedish/Finnish letters sorted after int''l sequence';

	Use hcNoContext if help contexts are not used.


    function  PxTblCreateBox(HC,hOK,hCanx: word; var Name: string) : boolean;

	Dialog box to create a table.

	Example:
	  If PxTblCreateBox(hcCreateBox,hcOK,hcCancel, TableName) then
		OpenTbl(TableName)

	The parameters given may be used for help contexts:

	  hcCreateBox:		Hint := 'Name of table to create';
	  hcCreateBox+1:	Hint := 'Enter a field name';
	  hcCreateBox+2:	Hint := 'Type codes:  A,M,N,$,S,D';
	  hcCreateBox+3:	Hint := 'Field length (Alpha and Memo fields only)';
	  hcCreateBox+4:	Hint := 'Index on field';

	Use hcNoContext if help contexts are not used.


